just_use referee.go

# label: ELEGANT
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Referee is stateless: show it a board and a proposed move, get a ruling.
It does not remember prior moves, does not track whose turn it is, does
not count moves per turn. Those are social rules, not physics.

Two entry points:
  ValidateGameMove — mid-turn ruling: protocol, geometry, inventory.
  ValidateTurnComplete — can this turn end? geometry + semantics.

Semantics (no Incomplete/Bogus/Dup stacks) are NOT checked mid-turn —
2-card stacks are legitimate in-progress states. Only at turn boundaries
must every stack be a valid group. This split is load-bearing.

Inventory check prevents both "card appeared from nowhere" and "hand card
declared played but not placed", plus catches duplicates on the post-move
board (double-deck awareness means same-rank+suit from different decks is
OK, but identical OriginDeck is not).
